<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@groupserver_layout/page">
  <head>
    <title metal:fill-slot="title">Invite New Group Members in Bulk</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div metal:fill-slot="messages"
         tal:define="result view/process_form;
                     isError python:result.get('error', False);"
         tal:condition="python:result and result.has_key('message')"
         tal:attributes="class python:(isError and 'message-error') or 'message-result'"
         tal:content="structure result/message"/>
    <ul metal:fill-slot="breadcrumb">
      <li class="site">
        <a tal:attributes="title string:${view/siteInfo/name} Homepage"
           href="/" title="Home" class="icon-alone">
          <span aria-hidden="true" data-icon="&#x2302;"></span>
          <span class="screen-reader-text"
                tal:content="string:${view/siteInfo/name} Homepage">Home</span></a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a class="group" 
           tal:attributes="href string:${view/groupInfo/relativeURL}/">
          <strong
            tal:content="view/groupInfo/name">This group</strong></a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span 
          tal:content="python:'Invite' if view.invite_only else 'Add'">Stuff</span>
        in bulk
      </li>
    </ul>
    <form metal:fill-slot="body" id="gs-group-member-invite-csv" 
          enctype="multipart/form-data" method="post" action="." 
          tal:attributes="action request/URL"
          tal:define="inviteAdd python:'Invite' if view.invite_only else 'Add'">
      <h1>
        <span 
          tal:content="inviteAdd">Add</span> New Group Members in Bulk
      </h1>
      <p>
        You can 
        <span tal:condition="view/invite_only">invite new members to join</span>
        <span tal:condition="not:view/invite_only">add new members to</span>
        <span class="group" 
              tal:content="view/groupInfo/name">this group</span>
        in bulk, using a spreadsheet.
      </p>
      <p tal:condition="not:view/invite_only"> 
        <strong>Please note:</strong> This should only be used when you
        have absolute certainty that the person wishes to be a member of
        the group, and you are certain of their details. If you are not,
        please use 
        <a tal:attributes="href
                           string:${view/groupInfo/url}/admin_join_invite_csv.html">Invite New Group Members in Bulk</a> instead.
      </p>
      <div id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-csv" role="region"
           aria-labelledby="gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-csv-h">
        <h2 id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-csv-h">
          Step 1: Create the CSV File
        </h2>
        <p>Create a CSV (comma-separated value) file.
        The file needs to contain all the profile information of all
        the members you wish to invite.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The file must contain at least 
          <strong>two rows:</strong> a header, and a
          row for each member that you wish to add.</li>
          <li> There must be at least two columns. First, an
          <samp>Email to</samp> column will contains the email 
          address that the invitation will be sent to.
          Second a <samp>Name</samp> column will contains the name of
          the person who is invited.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Expert administrators can also add extra columns, but this
          is not necessary.
          Experts should also note that you should not invite more
          than 127 members at any one time, as strange timeout issues
          can occur.
        </p>
      </div><!--gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-csv-->
      <div id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-select" role="region"
           aria-labelledby="gs-group-member-invite-csv-select-h">
        <h2 id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-select-h">
          Step 2: Select the CSV File
        </h2>
        <p>
          Save the spreadsheet in CSV format, and select it using the
          selector below.
        </p>
        <div class="form-widget required">
          <label title="The CSV file that contains the data for the new members (required)"
                 for="csvfile">CSV File</label>
          <input class="fileType" id="csvfile" name="csvfile" 
                 type="file"  />
        </div>
      </div><!--gs-group-member-invite-csv-select-->
      <div id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-columns" role="region"
           aria-labelledby="gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-columns-h">
        <h2 id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-columns-h">
          Step 3: Set the Columns
        </h2>
        <p>Now set the columns up.
        The columns below <strong>must</strong> match the columns in
        your spreadsheet.
        </p>
        <div id="columns"
             tal:define="shown string:display:block;;; hidden string:display:none;;;">
          <tal:block repeat="column view/columns">
            <div class="column disclosureWidget"
                 tal:define="n repeat/column/number;">
              <label for="#" class="disclosureButton"
                     tal:attributes="for column/columnId"
                     tal:content="column/columnTitle">Stuff</label>
              <div class="disclosureShowHide"
                   tal:define="startTwo python:n&lt;=len(view.requiredColumns);"
                   tal:attributes="style python:startTwo and shown or hidden;">
                <select id="#" name="#" 
                        tal:attributes="id column/columnId; name column/columnId">
                  <tal:block
                    repeat="option column/profileList">
                    <tal:block define="m repeat/option/number;
                                       req option/value/required;
                                       showReq python:req or option.token == 'toAddr';
                                       reqStr string:${option/title} (Required);
                                       optionContent python:showReq and reqStr or option.title;
                                       initial python:(n==1 and option.token == 'toAddr') or ((n&gt;1) and (((n-1)==m) and req))">
                      <option 
                        tal:condition="initial"
                        selected="selected"
                        tal:content="optionContent"
                        tal:define="m repeat/option/number"
                        tal:attributes="value option/token"/>
                      <option 
                        tal:condition="not:initial"
                        tal:content="optionContent"
                        tal:define="m repeat/option/number"
                        tal:attributes="value option/token"/>
                    </tal:block>
                  </tal:block>
                  <option tal:condition="startTwo"
                          value="nothing">(Unused)</option>
                  <option tal:condition="not:startTwo"
                          selected="selected" value="nothing">(Unused)</option>
                </select>
              </div><!--disclosureShowHide-->
            </div><!--disclosureWidget-->
          </tal:block>
        </div><!--columns-->  
      </div><!--gs-group-member-invite-csv-create-columns-->
      <div id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-settings" role="region"
           aria-labelledby="gs-group-member-invite-csv-settings-h">
        <h2 id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-settings-h">
          Step 4: Set the Message Delivery Settings
        </h2>
        <p>
          By default, new members will receive an email every time
          someone posts to 
          <span class="group" 
                tal:content="view/groupInfo/name">this group</span>.
          However, you can change this so the new members receive a
          daily digest of topics, or participate in the group using
          the web only.
        </p>
        <div class="radioItem">
          <input id="delivery.0" class="radioType" type="radio" 
                 value="email" name="delivery" checked="checked"/>
          <label class="radioLabel" for="delivery.0">One email per 
          post.</label>
        </div>
        <div class="radioItem">
          <input id="delivery.1" class="radioType" type="radio" 
                 value="digest" name="delivery"/>
          <label class="radioLabel" for="delivery.1">Daily digest of 
          topics.</label>
        </div>
        <div class="radioItem">
          <input id="delivery.2" class="radioType" type="radio" 
                 value="web" name="delivery"/>
          <label class="radioLabel" for="delivery.2">Web only</label>
        </div>
        <div class="noFloat">&#160;</div>
      </div><!--gs-group-member-invite-csv-settings-->
      <div id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-invite" role="region"
           aria-labelledby="gs-group-member-invite-csv-invite-h">
        <h2 id="gs-group-member-invite-csv-invite-h">
          Step 5: <span tal:content="inviteAdd">Invite</span> the Members
        </h2>
        <tal:block tal:condition="view/invite_only">
          <p>
            Click the 
            <samp class="button" tal:content="inviteAdd">Invite</samp> 
            button to invite the members specified in your CSV file.
            Each new member will be sent the following invitation message.
            (The URL itself will be different for each new member.)
          </p>
          <pre id="invite-message-preview"
             tal:define="text python:False;
                         preview python:True;
                         text python:True;
                         fromAddr string:foo;
                         toAddr string:bar;
                         supportAddr string:wibble;
                         subject string:Invitation to Join ${view/groupInfo/name};
                         body view/message;"
             tal:content="structure provider:groupserver.InvitationMessage">
            Preview
          </pre><!--invite-message-preview-->
        </tal:block>
        <input type="hidden" id="submitted" name="submitted" 
               class="hidden" value=""/>
        <input type="submit" id="create" name="create" class="btn"
               value="Chicken" tal:attributes="value inviteAdd"/>
      </div><!--gs-group-member-invite-csv-invite-->
    </form><!--gs-group-member-invite-csv-->
  </body>
</html>
